I've been eating here for the past 10 years and so my rating may be a bit biased due to the emotional attachment I have to the restaurant. I'm also Dominican and grew up eating the food  so I'm extra picky when it comes to eating Dominican food outside of my home (meaning it better be pretty damn good if I'm paying for it).  That being said, I usually order their chicharron de pollo with white rice and beans since it's always prepared very well.Their churrasco is also tasty. Their cuban sandwiches are alright, sometimes it is disappointing but for the most part it's on point. However, they have increased the pricing of the sandwiches throughout the years and the sandwiches haven't improved whatsoever in quality.  Overall, their portions are reasonable for the amount they charge and the quality of food is average. I've always taken my food to go so I don't know how they are as far as dining in goes, but they do provide pretty speedy and polite service at the counter.
The food is good and the waitresses are very nice. They have the best chicken around New York.
